GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 656
Short Title: Split Distr Ct/Defender Distr 43 into 43A/43B. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Clampitt.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Judiciary 1, if favorable, Appropriations, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and
Operations of the House
April 2, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO SPLIT DISTRICT COURT DISTRICT 43 INTO DISTRICT COURT DISTRICTS
3 43A AND 43B, TO SPLIT DEFENDER DISTRICT 43 INTO DEFENDER DISTRICTS
4 43A AND 43B, AND TO APPROPRIATE FUNDS.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1.(a) G.S. 7A-133 reads as rewritten:
7 "§ 7A-133. Numbers of judges by districts; numbers of magistrates and additional seats of
8 court, by counties.
9 (a) Each district court district shall have the numbers of judges as set forth in the
10 following table:
11
12 District Judges County
13 …
14 4343A 74 Cherokee
15 Clay
16 Graham
17 Haywood
18 Jackson
19 Macon
20 Swain.Swain
21 43B 4 Haywood
22 Jackson."
23 SECTION 1.(b) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Administrative
24 Office of the Courts the sum of two hundred fifty-three thousand one dollars ($253,001) in
25 recurring funds and ten thousand three hundred seventy-six dollars ($10,376) in nonrecurring
26 funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be used to hire one full-time district court judge pursuant
27 to Section 1(a) of this act.
28 SECTION 1.(c) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Administrative
29 Office of the Courts the sum of seven thousand four hundred twenty-one dollars ($7,421) in
30 recurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be added to the salary of the district court judge
31 selected as chief district court judge of District 43B created under Section 1(a) of this act.
32 SECTION 1.(d) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Administrative
33 Office of the Courts the sum of seventy-one thousand nine hundred thirty-two dollars ($71,932)
34 in recurring funds and three thousand four hundred thirty-six dollars ($3,436) in nonrecurring
*H656-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be used to hire one full-time judicial assistant to serve
2 District Court District 43B.
3 SECTION 1.(e) Subsection (a) of this section becomes effective January 1, 2027,
4 and elections held in 2026 shall be held accordingly. The remainder of this section becomes
5 effective July 1, 2026.
6 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 7A-498.7(a) reads as rewritten:
7 "(a) The following counties of the State are organized into the defender districts listed
8 below, and in each of those defender districts an office of public defender is established:
9
10 Defender District Counties
11 ___________________________________________________________________
12 …
13 4343A Cherokee, Clay, Graham,
14 Haywood, Jackson, Macon,
15 Swain
16 43B Haywood, Jackson
17 After notice to, and consultation with, the affected district bar, senior resident superior court
18 judge, and chief district court judge, the Commission on Indigent Defense Services may
19 recommend to the General Assembly that a district or regional public defender office be
20 established. A legislative act is required in order to establish a new office or to abolish an existing
21 office."
22 SECTION 2.(b) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Administrative
23 Office of the Courts, Office of Indigent Defense Services, the sum of two hundred twenty-eight
24 thousand four hundred sixty-one dollars ($228,461) in recurring funds and four thousand eight
25 hundred ninety-five dollars ($4,895) in nonrecurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be
26 used to hire one full-time chief public defender to serve Defender District 43B.
27 SECTION 2.(c) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Administrative
28 Office of the Courts, Office of Indigent Defense Services, the sum of four hundred twenty-four
29 thousand four hundred eighty-eight dollars ($424,488) in recurring funds and fourteen thousand
30 six hundred eighty-five dollars ($14,685) in nonrecurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to
31 be used to hire three full-time assistant public defenders to serve Defender District 43B.
32 SECTION 2.(d) This section becomes effective July 1, 2026.
33 SECTION 3. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
34 law.
